Quote:  <i>Belt-vanners</i>: Machines consisting of a short but wide, inclined, moving, rubber belt on which the pulverised ore was washed by a counter-flow of water to separate the concentrates, washing away the lighter material and leaving the heavy sulphides to be discharged at the top end. ...
